                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman</hi>). I was with Smith—I produce some knives and forks which I got at the Bell.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-444" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-444" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-444" type="surname" value="GREY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-444" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH GREY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am bar-maid at the Bell, in Basinghall-street, kept by Mr. Robinson. On 17th Aug. the prisoner brought these knives and forks (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)—Mrs. Robinson bought them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PARRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What did she give for them? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for six—he said, "They belong to Miss Bailey, at our house," and she was obliged to part with them, as she was unfortunate.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-445" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-445" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-445" type="surname" value="DABBS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-445" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED DABBS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker. I produce a counterpane, pawned on 8th April, by a man—this duplicate produced by Smith is the one I gave.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
